cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with single-target tracker performance evaluation and proposes a new evaluation methodology with a fully-annotated dataset with visual attributes. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the proposed methodology aims at statistical significance and practical differences, which are important in AI research. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the proposed methodology involves ranking-based evaluation, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with video tracking and proposes a new dataset with diverse visual properties. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the proposed evaluation system allows easy integration of third-party trackers, which could be useful in robotics applications.
